sec.p:
It has been well-established in the literature that the standard asymptotic theory cannot be used to test for hypothesis in a level VAR model if the series are nonstationary (Sims et al. 1990; Toda and Phillips 1993). To avoid this problem, Emirmahmutoglu and Kose (2011) proposed an alternative method to test coefficient restrictions of a level VAR model. This method is based on the modified Wald test in the lag-augmented VAR (LA-VAR) approach with the asymptotic chi-square (χ) distribution for the estimated VAR (p + dmax) model. Emirmahmutoglu and Kose (2011) extended the LA-VAR approach to test panel causality for heterogeneous mixed panels.1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
